                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12423599" author="andreask" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2006 10:09:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test code (TestProto is packed into derbyTesting.jar), does new Socket(hostName, 1527). derbyTesting.jar does not have permission to connect and resolve. Fix could be to grant permission in testProtocol.policy.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12423619" author="andreask" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2006 11:12:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1545&quot; title=&quot;derbynet/testProtocol.java fails with security manager enabled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1545&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1545&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.diff + stat) which gives socket permission to derbyTesting.jar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12423624" author="knutanders" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2006 11:43:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for looking into the issue, Andreas! I looked at the patch and verified that it fixes the problem. +1 to commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12423647" author="andreask" created="Wed, 26 Jul 2006 13:40:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 425732.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12423828" author="andreask" created="Thu, 27 Jul 2006 12:43:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Improved the original patch by also granting permission to &quot;${derbyTesting.serverhost}&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
This should make it possible to also run this test when the server host is on a remote machine.&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 426048.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
